data.name: Callisons
data.description: Callisons is on a mission to make the flavor process simple. For over 120 years we have innovated and adapted to the natural products market and that journey has brought us to the flavor company we are today. Today, we utilize our experience to proactively bring our partners a personalized flavor experience that meets their goals. Whether that is new product development, pushing a product over the finish line or reducing costs of current flavors, our goal is to take the stress out of the process. Callisons is excited to take on the challenge of developing the perfect flavor for your food, beverage, and personal care products!

data.name: Mint Oils
data.description: Since 1903, Callisons has been innovating and developing mint flavor profiles for customers in nearly every region on earth. We are direct-to-source in every major growing region, allowing us access to the highest quality oils. Our Mint oils are representative of standard oils from each region.

data.name: Versa
data.description: Our Versa™ platform takes your new and existing flavors to new heights. We work with you to enhance, mask or add signature notes to your products.

data.name: Toothpaste and Mouthwash Flavors
data.description: Are you looking for a smooth, clean mint profile?  Intense cooling? Whether you are developing a new toothpaste or mouthwash product, Callisons has the perfect flavor for your brand. We have a library of market ready, on trend flavors for the toothpaste and mouthwash segments.

data.name: Alcohol Inspired Flavors
data.description: As the rise in non-alcohol adult beverage continues and category crossover expands, the need for alcohol type flavors will grow as well.  Callisons has developed a line of alcohol type flavors ranging from beer to wine and spirits that are perfect for alcohol and non-alcohol beverage, confection and more.

data.name: Hemp Flavors
data.description: As hemp becomes more mainstream, consumers are looking for unique products that provide distinctively green and earthy flavor profiles. As a result, many large beverage, confectionery and nutritional brands have started to incorporate some of these notes into their products. Callisons hemp and cannabis flavors were developed to replicate actual strains without any of the active ingredients.

data.name: Nutritional and Sport Drink Flavors
Oral Care Flavors Cool Mint Flavor N&A OS (109908)
data.description:
Flavor Description: Refresh your tastebuds to start the day with Callisons Cool Mint flavor. This flavor was designed to feature a strong North American mint profile with accents of eucalyptus and spice. This product is perfect for mouth rinse applications.

Target Region: North America

End Use Application: Oral Care, Mouth Rinse

Solubility: Oil Soluble

Use Level: 0.20 – 0.50%

Sample Size: 1 oz.

data.name: Oral Care Flavors Honey Apricot Spice Flavor N&A OS (110280)
data.description: Oral Care Flavors Honey Apricot Spice Flavor N&A OS (110280) is a combination of sweet, fruity apricot notes with hints of spice. This product was developed to deliver exceptional flavor for various oral care applications. This product is oil soluble.

data.name: Callisons Plum Flavor NAT WONF WS (1823112)
data.description: Callisons Plum Flavor NAT WONF WS (1823112) is an exquisite blend of sweet, floral, and fruity notes delicately accented by hints of grape-like flavor. Crafted to perfection, this flavor masterpiece is versatile, seamlessly enhancing a myriad of applications, from oral care and confections to beverages and beyond.

data.name: Callisons Dragon Starfruit Type Flavor N&A SD (111450)
data.description: Callisons Dragon Starfruit Type Flavor N&A SD (111450) captures the delightful blend of sweet, sour, and stone fruit notes, complemented by subtle hints of citrus. Perfect for enhancing Protein powders, Pre-Workout mixes, Dry beverages, Protein bars, Snack bars, and more. Its spray-dry solubility ensures easy integration.

data.name: Callisons Wintergreen Flavor N&A WS (111971)
data.description: Callisons Wintergreen Flavor N&A WS (111971) is a wintergreen flavoring agent. It is in a liquid state, appears colorless, and has a characteristic odor, which is typically associated with the wintergreen flavor. This flavor is used in various food and beverage applications to impart a refreshing and minty taste reminiscent of wintergreen.

data.name: Callisons Chocolate Mint Type Flavor (108669)
data.description: Callisons Chocolate Mint Type Flavor (108669) has subtle notes of cocoa and hints of mint. This combination delivers a delectable flavor to various applications in the beverage space, baked goods, confectionary market and more. This is a liquid flavor and water soluble.

data.name: Callisons Butter Type Flavor, NAT WS (111200)
data.description: Callisons Butter Type Flavor, NAT WS (111200), enables you to achieve the sumptuous richness of a full butter product while using less butter. Tailored for muffins, cookies, cinnamon rolls, snack bars, baking mixes, and more, this flavor solution enhances your culinary creations effortlessly.

data.name: Callisons Lemon Lime Type Flavor NAT SD (109065)
data.description: Callisons Lemon Lime Type Flavor NAT SD (109065) offers a delightful blend of zesty, sweet, and balanced notes of lime and lemon. Ideal for enhancing protein powders, pre-workout mixes, dry beverages, protein bars, and snack bars, this flavor's spray-dry solubility ensures easy incorporation into various products.

data.name: Oral Care Flavors Mint Flavor N&A OS (112554)
data.description: Oral Care Flavors Mint Flavor N&A OS (112554) has an exceptional minty flavor that has tones of frosty peppermint breeze. It was developed to enhance oral care products with a high-quality mint flavor that leaves your mouth feeling refreshed, best suited for use within various oral care applications. This product is oil soluble.

data.name: Arvensis Oil NAT (106109)
data.description: Mint Oils Arvensis Oil Indian NAT (106109) is characterized by a blend of high menthol content and subtle green notes. Its strong cooling effect makes it ideal for cost-effective confectionery and oral care applications, making it a versatile liquid oil.

data.name: Arvensis Oil Triple RECT NAT (105104)
data.description: Mint Oils India Arvensis Triple RECT NAT (105104) is an ideal choice either as a standalone flavor or as an ingredient in other blends. This oil imparts a classic mint-type flavor accompanied by refreshing cooling, making it suitable for a wide range of applications, from oral care to confection.

data.name: Dementholized Arvensis Oil NAT (105101)
data.description: Mint Oils India Dementholized Arvensis NAT (105101) presents a distinctive offering arising from arvensis oil with extracted menthol. This unique product exudes a sharp, green, and earthy odor and flavor profile. Tailored for applications in oral care and confectionery flavors, it lends its character to a variety of formulations, including toothpaste, mouth rinse, gum, chocolate, and more.

data.name: Peppermint Oil NAT (105109)
data.description: Mint Oils India Peppermint NAT (105109) captures the essence of India's mint oil production excellence. With robust cooling notes and a bold, full flavor profile, this oil epitomizes quality. Ideal for enhancing finished oral care, confection, and nutrition flavors, it adds depth and character to a diverse range of applications, including toothpaste, mouth rinse, gum, chocolate, and more.

data.name: Spearmint Oil 60% (105112)

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance
items: The Food Allergen Labeling & Consumer Protection Act of 2004 (FALCPA)

data.description: Callisons Spearmint Oil Indian 60% (105112) is a high-quality liquid product composed primarily of Indian spearmint oil, making up 60% of its formulation. This product is notable for its adherence to dietary preferences and requirements, being both Kosher and Halal certified. In addition, it is GMO-free, gluten-free, and a suitable choice for individuals following vegan and vegetarian diets. The sole ingredient in this product is spearmint oil.

data.name: Peppermint Willamette Type NAT OS (111069)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Warm, Full, Lactonic, Soft

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition

Description: This growing area is in the Willamette Valley, which ranges from west central to northwestern Oregon.

Elevation:180 – 230 ft (54 – 70 m)

Irrigation: The Willamette Valley is irrigated with wheel-line sprinklers, center pivots, and big guns with water in the lower valley primarily pumped from shallow wells that reach into the high water table. In the north and mid-valley areas, the water is supplied from the Willamette River and from slightly deeper wells.

data.name: Peppermint Idaho Type NAT OS (111074)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Fatty, Earthy, Green

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition

Description: This region, also called EO&I (Eastern Oregon and Idaho), is located on the Snake River Plain in the central border region of Oregon and Idaho. It spreads between Glenns Ferry, Idaho and Ontario, Oregon.

Elevation: 2200 - 3500 ft (671 - 1067 m)

Irrigation: Irrigation water for this region comes mainly from 5 area reservoirs and the Snake and Boise Rivers. 60% of crops in the area are flood-irrigated, with the remaining 40% sprinkled.

data.name: Peppermint Midwest Type NAT OS (111075)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Heavy, Earthy, Smoky, Warm

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition

Description: This growing region is spread out over three states. It encompasses Northern Indiana, Southern Wisconsin and Central Michigan

Elevation: 700 – 900 ft (213 – 275 m)

Irrigation: Each year a greater amount of the land is irrigated. About 50% of the mint fields are irrigated. Irrigation is done by big guns or center pivots. Water for this purpose is pulled from wells or drainage ditches that are backed up from rivers.

data.name: Peppermint Yakima Type NAT OS (111076)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Full, Heavy, Diesel, Herbal

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition

Description: This region is composed of three main growing areas: the Yakima Valley (south-central Washington), the Columbia Basin (central Washington), and the Hermiston/Boardman area (northern Oregon).

Elevation: 650 – 1200 ft (198 – 366 m)

Irrigation: The Columbia Basin and Hermiston/Boardman areas are primarily sprinkle irrigated with water from the Columbia River. The Yakima River and its five mountain reservoirs provide irrigation water for the Yakima Valley, which is mostly rill or flood irrigated.

data.name: Spearmint Oil Native Type (111079)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Herbal, Spicy, Green, Full

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition

data.name: Spearmint Oil Scotch Type (111080)
data.description:
Mint Oil Profile: Buttery, Sharp, Thin

Uses: Oral Care, Confection, Personal Care, Nutrition
